-- 046_settings_email_template_translations.sql
-- Translates the remaining Organization Settings UI that lived in PHP
-- arrays (invisible to the automated view-wiring): the Email Templates
-- catalog labels/recipients/placeholder descriptions
-- (EmailTemplate::definitions()), the notification-channel rows,
-- timezone/mail-history/member-field labels in
-- views/settings/municipality.php, and authority event_singular terms.
-- Email subject/body defaults stay Greek deliberately: they are sent
-- content, customizable per organization. The settings/municipality.244
-- 'el' value ends in a Latin semicolon, built via CHAR(59) because
-- MigrationRunner splits statements on raw semicolons.
-- Idempotent (ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE).

